A new cancer vaccine could teach the immune system to "see" bad cells
A new cancer vaccine can teach the immune system to "see" bad cells and destroy them
 The vaccine teaches the immune system to recognize bad cells as part of the treatment
The procedure involves extracting immune cells from the patient and replacing them in the laboratory
